      "lesson title": "AI in Travel Planning: Misinformation Risks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores the growing use of artificial intelligence tools in travel planning and the potential risks that come with relying on them too heavily. AI systems can generate confident-sounding travel advice that is outdated, inaccurate, or entirely fabricated, including incorrect visa requirements, non-existent hotels, and faulty flight information. As a beginner, you will learn how to spot common warning signs of AI-generated misinformation and understand why verifying travel details through official and trusted sources is so important. The lesson offers practical guidance on how to use AI tools sensibly as a starting point rather than a definitive source of truth. By the end, you will feel more confident in your ability to plan trips safely and avoid costly mistakes caused by inaccurate AI-generated itineraries or advice.",
